events.name: Study Jam (Android Development for Beginners)
events.description:
Let's get together and start Jamming!

Study Jam dates: 14th,21st, 28th of Jan, and 4th, 11th, 18th of Feb. (Total of 6 meetings)

Google Developers Study Jams is a series of an in-person study groups to support students taking online Udacity courses on Google developer technologies. These events are run by local Google Developer Groups or other developer meetups all over the world. Study Jams are run around the Udacity Android for Beginners course.

The mission of Study Jams is to provide a supplement to the online course experience with a live community learning environment will support students in completing the course and achieving certification. The goal is to provide deeper understanding in the course material within a fun and collaborative community environment.

Study Jams are an opportunity for students to receive free, in-person guidance and tutoring on the Udacity course in a fun classroom environment.

All are welcome to join a Study Jam, though students should first be sure to meet the course prerequisites and requirements. Here are the Udacity course requirements. This course is intended for beginners. Students with a higher level of programming experience, but want to get started on programming for Android Apps are also welcome. You will be expected to download Android Studio (http://developer.android.com/sdk/installing/studio.html) in order to follow along with the instructors throughout the course. Access to an Android device is helpful, but not required, to complete the final project. Please see Technology Requirements (https://www.udacity.com/tech-requirements) for using Udacity.

Sign up now! limited spaces....

events.name: WTM Kuwait inauguration + Workshop on Web Security
events.description:
ندعوكم لاولى فعاليات صناع التقنية النسائية - شركة جوجل الأمن مع ورشة تطبيقات الويب مهندس أمن المعلومات/ محمد الدوب

لنتعرف على :

‏- لماذا يجب أن نحمي تطبيقات الويب؟- الهجمات على تطبيقات الويب- التطبيقات ذات القدرات الدفاعية- الحماية في الحوسبة السحابية

الأربعاء ١٢:٣٠-٢:٠٠ مساء حرم جامعة الكويت - الخالديةبالتعاون مع نادي كليك آي تي ومنظمة ArabWIC

م.محمد الدوب في سطور:مهندس ومتخصص في أمن المعلومات مدرب معتمد حائز على شهادات عالمية معتمدة في مجال أمن المعلومات مثل CISSP، CEH، GWAPT، ISO27001، ISO31000، له مشاركات في مجالات تطوعية في تقنيات الخصوصية رئيس فرع الكويت لمنظمة OWASP المعنية بأمن تطبيقات الويب.

Come and join us in announcing the Women Tech Makers WTM Kuwait community part of Google Developer Group and Google. In addition, join in on a workshop on Website Security by Engr. Mohammad AlDoob. In collaboration with ClickIT club and ArabWIC Kuwait.

On Wednesday 4th Oct 2017 at Kuwait University Khaldiya Campus

Workshop overview:1) Why secure the Web? 2) Web application attacks 3) Defensible applications 4) Security in the could

Speaker bio:

Engr. Mohammad Aldoob is specialist in information security and a certified trainer in security such as CISSP، CEH، GWAPT، ISO27001، ISO31000. He is an avid volunteer in technical areas and the leader of the Open Web Application Security Project for Web applications in Kuwait.

Note the WTM introduction will be in English and the workshop is in Arabic if english only speakers are not present.

events.name: Website Development Part 1 (for beginners)
events.description:
We will have a 7 day workshop on website development with two of our Lead WTM members and professional developers Ms. Sundus AlFaresi and Dr. Mariam AlHilal.
The event will cover HTML, CSS, Javascript, front-end and overview of back-end development.
Workshop dates are: Nov 20, 22, 27, 29 and Dec 4, 6. Final demos and certificates will be handed out on Dec 11th.

The event is open for everyone who registers through Meetup and is free. Attendees have to bring their own laptop with Atom installed. Failing to attend more than one day will result in no certificate.

events.name: Website Development Workshop (Part 1 for Beginners)
events.description:
The Women TechMakers - Kuwait Branch (Google chapter) invites you to attend FREE workshop under the name "Website Development" in collaboration with ClickIT club, and ArabWIC.

With website programmers and Mobile Developers Sundus AlFaresi, Saqiba Sulaiman and Dr. Mariam AlHilal
On Nov 25,27,29
Dec 4,7,11,13 at promenade cultural center , promenade Hawaly mall

Workshop overview:

1- how to be a programmer
2- build your own website
3- learn the latest programming SDK
4- basic programming commands HTML, CSS, and JavaScript
Speaker bio:
Ms. Sundus Alfaresi is specialist in computer science and a certified programmer from IBM and ITIL, she is an avid volunteer in technical areas and a journalist at Academy
Ms. Saqiba Sulaiman is online Information systems professional with over 9 years experience applying system analysis and technologies for improving online information management systems. Experience in process and data modelling, quality assurance, web development and project management.
Dr. Mariam AlHilal is a PhD graduate in Nutrition, Research associate in Dasman Diabetic Institute, Coded graduate, Full Stack Web Developer (Python, Django, Java Script, HTML5, CSS3, Intro to Swift). To register RSVP using this link:
https://www.meetup.com/wtm-kuwait/events/

Note:

*Missing more than three hours of workshops results in NO certificate.

*The workshop is for men and women interested in learning coding for basic website development.

*There will be a phone call interview before the workshop starts.

events.name: Android Development for Beginners - Study Jam
events.description:
Workshop dates: Thursdays 18th, 25th of Jan, and 1st, 8th of Feb . (Total of 4 meetings)

Google Developers Study Jams is a free series of global, community-run, in-person study groups. The current Study Jams series is presented in partnership with Udacity and will follow their Android for Beginners curriculum.

Study Jam sessions are designed around the Udacity course structure, with a weekly session following each lesson, plus two to three additional weeks for completing and sharing course final projects. Students are expected to come to the Study Jam sessions having completed that week’s Udacity lesson online, so that the Study Jam time may be used to review key concepts, address questions, and work on individual projects. Study Jam sessions are led by facilitators who are certified in the Udacity Android for Beginners course and adjust teaching to the students in the class.

This workshop is an opportunity for students to receive free, in-person guidance and tutoring in a fun classroom environment. All are welcome to join. This course is intended for beginners. Students with a higher level of programming experience, but want to get started on programming for Android Apps are also welcome. You will be expected to download Android Studio (http://developer.android.com/sdk/installing/studio.html) in order to follow along with the instructors throughout the course. Access to an Android device is helpful, but not required, to complete the final project. Please see Technology Requirements (https://www.udacity.com/tech-requirements) for using Udacity.

Sign up now!

events.name: Mobile Sites certification by Google
events.description:
WHAT IS MOBILE SITES CERTIFICATION?
Year after year, mobility is increasing. More and more people are consuming content on their mobile devices as compared to doing it on laptops/desktops.

Businesses and organisations compete for better user engagement and more conversions on mobile sites. It is thereby important, that developers and designers create experiences that serves the purpose.

With the Mobile Sites certification, Google accredits professionals who understand the mobile landscape and are well aware of the best practices to create superfast web pages and a smooth and amazing user experience for the mobile web. IS THE MOBILE SITES CERTIFICATION WORTH IT?
Mobile Sites Certification will not only help you stand out from the crowd, it'll also show that you have what it takes to succeed.
Being certified means being tested, which adds more trust and credibility to your profile. This helps you get more visibility to recruiters and hiring managers.
It can help you with new opportunities and higher salaries as well as help you retain your current job, which also is very important.
A certification can help fulfill both professional and personal goals, which is satisfying and rewarding in it's own sense.
The certification is FREE as of now, so go get it.

You may have the required skills, but, by having the certification, you get accredited by none other than Google, which definitely would prove valuable in one way or the other.

WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW?
The Mobile Sites certification is primarily for web developers and designers, whether experienced or fresher. If you have a prior coding experience, it won't hurt, but the certification tests more on the conceptual side of developing and designing for better mobile experiences. It won't test you on your coding skills, but rather will test you on best practices in developing faster web pages for mobile and creating effective mobile experiences.

This certification is for freshers and experienced alike. There are online study material links which experienced can REFER to and freshers can LEARN from, before appearing for the certification exam. There is a practice test with 68 questions that will clearly help you understand the types of questions that might be asked and their level of difficulty. A combination of study links and practice test is the key to achieve the certification. WHAT'S COVERED?
Detailed overview of the certification.
Tips and Tricks to clear the exam in the first attempt.
Links to online study/reference material, in case you need it.
68 hand-picked practice questions with answers and detailed explanations

WHAT ARE THE REQUIREMENTS?
Basics knowledge of how websites are built

WHAT AM I GOING TO GET FROM THIS COURSE?
Get detailed exam overview and proven passing strategy
Learn/Review required concepts under 3hrs, with an interactive online study reference
Download the certificate and add it to online profiles and resume
Get listed on Google Partners public profile

WHAT TO BRING
Get your own laptops and chargers. If possible get your own internet device!

WHAT IS THE TARGET AUDIENCE?
Web Developers and UI/UX Designers looking to add authenticity for the In-Demand skills
Freelance developers who wish to onboard more projects and clients by showcasing the earned certification
Students/Freshers wanting to start their careers in web development and design
Anyone, who wishes to get accredited by Google on the mobile landscape

P.S: THIS IS A THREE SESSIONS COURSE, 2 HOURS EACH.
events.how_to_find_us: Hall 109 is opposite the cafeteria, near the computer labs.  الموقع:gate 7 is open https://maps.google.com/?q=29.321272,47.972515

With the Mobile Sites certification, Google accredits professionals who understand the mobile landscape and are well aware of the best practices to create superfast web pages and a smooth and amazing user experience for the mobile web. IS THE MOBILE SITES CERTIFICATION WORTH IT?
Mobile Sites Certification will not only help you stand out from the crowd, it'll also show that you have what it takes to succeed.
Being certified means being tested, which adds more trust and credibility to your profile. This helps you get more visibility to recruiters and hiring managers.
It can help you with new opportunities and higher salaries as well as help you retain your current job, which also is very important.
A certification can help fulfill both professional and personal goals, which is satisfying and rewarding in it's own sense.
The certification is FREE as of now, so go get it.

You may have the required skills, but, by having the certification, you get accredited by none other than Google, which definitely would prove valuable in one way or the other.

WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW?
The Mobile Sites certification is primarily for web developers and designers, whether experienced or fresher. If you have a prior coding experience, it won't hurt, but the certification tests more on the conceptual side of developing and designing for better mobile experiences. It won't test you on your coding skills, but rather will test you on best practices in developing faster web pages for mobile and creating effective mobile experiences.

This certification is for freshers and experienced alike. There are online study material links which experienced can REFER to and freshers can LEARN from, before appearing for the certification exam. There is a practice test with 68 questions that will clearly help you understand the types of questions that might be asked and their level of difficulty. A combination of study links and practice test is the key to achieve the certification. WHAT'S COVERED?
Detailed overview of the certification.
Tips and Tricks to clear the exam in the first attempt.
Links to online study/reference material, in case you need it.
68 hand-picked practice questions with answers and detailed explanations

WHAT ARE THE REQUIREMENTS?
Basics knowledge of how websites are built

WHAT AM I GOING TO GET FROM THIS COURSE?
Get detailed exam overview and proven passing strategy
Learn/Review required concepts under 3hrs, with an interactive online study reference
Download the certificate and add it to online profiles and resume
Get listed on Google Partners public profile

WHAT TO BRING
Get your own laptops and chargers. If possible get your own internet device!

WHAT IS THE TARGET AUDIENCE?
Web Developers and UI/UX Designers looking to add authenticity for the In-Demand skills
Freelance developers who wish to onboard more projects and clients by showcasing the earned certification
Students/Freshers wanting to start their careers in web development and design
Anyone, who wishes to get accredited by Google on the mobile landscape

P.S: THIS IS A THREE SESSIONS COURSE, 2 HOURS EACH.

events.name: Machine Learning with TensorFlow Crash Course (ML, TF)
events.description:
Curious about machine learning? Come to this event and learn how to get started!
Free elevation burger too! 👍🏻

The best part about developing with machine learning today is that you can get started with no prior experience.

Dr. Abdullah AlMutairi from College of Computing Sciences and Engineering at Kuwait University will be presenting an introduction into machine learning and applications in Tensor Flow.

At this event, Dr. Abdullah AlMutairi will introduce Machine Learning basics, and TensorFlow, an open source library for machine intelligence. Then we’ll work through some codelabs (guided step by step tutorials). Please bring a laptop and charger.

Both topics need a long time to master but we are hoping to show interested developers how to started (especially with the ready to use APIs, and perhaps the basic
TensorFlow tutorials) ­ even if they’re entirely new to the field.

Title: How­To Start Developing with Machine Learning

Agenda:
6pm Guests arrive
6:30pm Machine learning basics and TensorFLow
7:30pm Break
7:45pm Coding session
8:45pm Socialize

What is Google’s Machine Learning developer platform?
By Google’s Machine Learning developer platform, we mean all the resources we have to help
developers who want to use machine learning. Broadly speaking, it can be divided into three
parts.

Machine Learning:
Ready ­to ­use APIs
The best part about developing with ML today is that you can get started with no prior experience.
● Google Cloud Platform provides APIs for Vision, Natural Language, Speech, and Translation.
● Mobile Vision provides APIs for Face Detection, Text Recognition, and Barcode Scanning on Android and iOS
● All of these have a simple interface
● None require prior experience with machine learning

TensorFlow:

TensorFlow is an open source library for machine learning. And it’s the most popular ML library
on Github.
● TensorFlow is used by researchers, data scientists, and developers.
● TensorFlow is capable of large­scale machine learning, and it is production­ready.
● If you’re new to machine learning, you can use TensorFlow to explore (we encourage
you do so, and dive in!) There are tutorials (like Beginners MNIST) that are accessible to
novices. Others are for experienced machine learning developers.
Managed Services

Finally, we have managed services to support more complex use­cases.
● Cloud Machine Learning is a platform for building, training, and running custom models
of almost any size, on Google’s infrastructure.
● Currently in “alpha”, but good to be aware of down the road.

• What to bring
Laptop, charger and a curious mind.
